If it was possible, it probably would have been done on the C64 first.  It doesn't have enough RAM either, 64kB I guess.  A quick google search turns up something called Lunix, that might be adaptable to some degree but I don't know what one would do with it (and you would still need a custom NES cart board with more RAM).<br /><br />If just an operating system in general is interesting, look into embedded systems and RTOS (real-time operating system).  Even those are probably outgrowing the NES in general, but I'm sure there are even little OS type things running on many microcontrollers that have a lot less RAM than the NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Wed Jul 21, 2010 3:51 pm</p><hr />
