<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6636&amp;p=64588#p64588"><![CDATA[
Impossible.  Linux on the DS needs 2MB of RAM.  NES has 2k, or 10k with a typical expansion from the cartridge.<br /><br />Even if you made a huge RAM cartridge, and somehow got all the C code to compile for the NES, and took care of the bankswitching needed to address all the ram, it would be unbelievably slow.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Wed Jul 21, 2010 1:43 pm</p><hr />
